obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47675)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st May, 1922, see Gen. R. & O., Vol. V, p. 49; Gazette of India, 1922, Pt. I, p. 384.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47675&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi University Act, 1922.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such^1`
  line `date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47676)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47676&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act and in the Statutes, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,
  line
  line `^1[(a) "College" means an institution maintained or admitted to its privileges by the University,`
  line `and includes an Affiliated College and a Constituent College;`
  line
  line `Explanation-- IAffiliated College" means an institution recognized by the University in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act and the Statutes in which instruction is provided in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Statutes and Ordinances up to the Bachelor's degree but`
  line `exclusive of Honours and post-graduate degrees;`
  line
  line `Explanation II--.Constituent College" means an institution recognized as such by the Executive`
  line `Council in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(b) "Hall" means a unit of residence for students of the University provided, maintained or`
  line `recognized by it.]`
  line
  line `(c) "Patron of the University" means a person who has made a donation of not less than one`
  line `lakh of rupees to the funds of the University, and has been declared by the Chancellor to be a`
  line `patron of the University;`
  line
  line `(d) "Principal" means the head of a College ^2[and includes, when there is no Principal, the`
  line `person for the time being duly appointed to act as principal, and, in the absence of the principal or`
  line `the acting principal, a Vice-Principal duly appointed as such;]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) "Statutes", "Ordinances" and "Regulations" means, respectively, the Statutes, Ordinances`
  line `and Regulations of the University made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "teachers" includes Professors, Readers, Lecturers and other persons imparting instruction`
  line `in the University or in any College or Hall;`
  line
  line `^4[(h) "teachers of the University means persons appointed or recognized by the University for`
  line `the purpose of imparting instruction in the University or in any College;]`
  line
  line `(i) "University" means the University of Delhi; and`
  line
  line `(j) "Warden" means the head of a Hall.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 3, for clauses (a) and (b).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 24 of 1943, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Clause (e) omitted by Act 5 of 1952, s. 3.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (h).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47677)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `The University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47677&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Chancellor and the first Vice-Chancellor of the University`
  line `and the first members of the Court, the Executive Council and the Academic Council and all`
  line `persons who may hereafter become such officers or members, so long as they continue to hold such`
  line `office or membership, are hereby constituted a body corporate by the name of the University of`
  line `Delhi".`
  line
  line `(2) The University shall have perpetual succession and a common seal, and shall sue and be`
  line `sued by the said name.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47678)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Powers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47678&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The University shall have the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) to provide for instruction in such branches of learning as the University may think fit, and`
  line `to make provision for research and for the advancement and dissemination of knowledge.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) to hold examinations and to grant to, and confer degrees and other academic`
  line `distinctions on, persons who--`
  line
  line `(a) have pursued a course of study in the University or in any College, or`
  line
  line `(b) are non-collegiate women students residing within the territorial jurisdiction of the`
  line `University, or`
  line
  line `(c) are teachers in educational institutions under conditions laid down in the Statutes and`
  line `Ordinances and have passed the examinations of the University under like conditions], ^2[or]`
  line
  line `^2[(d) have pursued a course of study by correspondence, whether residing within the`
  line `territorial jurisdiction of the University or not], ^3[or]`
  line
  line `^3[(e) have been registered by the University, subject to such conditions as may be laid`
  line `down in the Statutes and Ordinances, as external candidates, being persons residing within`
  line `the territorial limits to which the powers of the University extend],.`
  line
  line `(3) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions on approved persons in the manner laid`
  line `down in the Statutes,`
  line
  line `(4) to grant such diplomas to, and to provide such lectures and instruction for, persons not`
  line `being members of the University, as the University may determine,`
  line
  line `(5) to co-operate with other Universities and authorities in such manner and for such`
  line `purposes as the University may determine,`
  line
  line `(6) to institute Professorships, Readerships, Lecturerships and any other teaching posts`
  line `required by the University,`
  line
  line `(7) to appoint or recognise persons as Professors, Readers or Lecturers, or otherwise as`
  line `teachers of the University,`
  line
  line `(8) to institute and award Fellowships, Scholarships, Exhibitions and Prizes ^4 ***`
  line
  line `^5[(9) to maintain Colleges and Halls, to admit to its privileges Colleges not maintained by the`
  line `University and to withdraw all or any of those privileges, and to recognize Halls not maintained`
  line `by the University and to withdraw any such recognition],`
  line
  line `^6[(9A) to declare, with the consent of the colleges concerned, in the manner specified by the`
  line `Academic Council, colleges conducting courses of study in the Faculties of Medicine, Technology,`
  line `Music or Fine Arts, as autonomous colleges:`
  line
  line `Provided that the extent of the autonomy which each such college may have, and the matters in`
  line `relation to which it may exercise such autonomy, shall be such as may be prescribed by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(9B) to set up one or more College Administrative Councils for two or more colleges with such`
  line `composition, powers and functions as may be laid down in the Statutes],`
  line
  line `(10) to demand and receive payment of such fees and other charges as may be authorized by the`
  line Ordinances,
  line
  line `(11) to supervise and control the residence and discipline of students of the University, and to`
  line `make arrangements for promoting their health and general welfare,`
  line
  line `^7[(11A) to make grants from the funds of the University for assistance to forms of extramural`
  line teaching],
  line
  line `^8[(12) to make special arrangements in respect of the residence, discipline and teaching of women`
  line students,]
  line
  line `^9[(12A) to acquire, hold, manage and dispose of property movable or immovable, including trust or`
  line `endowed property, for the purposes of the University,`
  line
  line `(12B) with the approval Of the Central Government, to borrow, on the security of University`
  line `property, money for the purposes of the University,]`
  line
  line `^10[(12C) to create administrative and ministerial and other necessary posts and to make`
  line `appointments thereto, and]`
  line
  line `(13) to do all such other acts and things, whether incidental to the powers aforesaid or not, as may`
  line `be requisite in order to further the objects of the University as a teaching and examining body, and to`
  line `cultivate and promote arts, science and other branches of learning`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 4, for clause (2).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 61 of 1961, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1962).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 1970, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-6-1970).`
  line
  line `4. The words "In accordance with the Statutes and the Regulations" omitted by Act 5 of 1952, s. 4.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (9).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 48 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-6-1972).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 24 of 1943, s. 3.`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 4, for clause (12).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 61 of 1961, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1962).`
  line
  line `10. Clause (12A) renumbered as clause (12C) by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47679)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Territorial exercise of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47679&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the powers of the`
  line `University conferred by or under this Act ^1[(other than those conferred by sub-clause (d) of clause 2`
  line `of section 4)] shall not extend ^2[beyond the limits of the ^3[Union territory of Delhi]], and`
  line `notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force, no educational institution`
  line `beyond ^4[those limits] shall be associated with or admitted to any privileges of the University.`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, if it`
  line `is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, direct, by order in writing,`
  line `the University to admit to its privileges any institution situated outside India and the University shall`
  line `be bound to comply with such direction.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything in any other law for the time being in force ^7[but subject to the`
  line `provisions contained in the Jawaharlal Nehru University Act, 1966 (53 of 1966)], no educational institution within the ^8[aforementioned limits] shall be associated in any way with or be admitted`
  line `to any privileges of any other University incorporated by law in the States, and any such privileges`
  line `granted by any such other University to any educational institution within ^9[those limits] prior to the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall be deemed to be withdrawn on the commencement of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by order^10 in writing, direct that the provisions of this`
  line `sub-section shall not apply in the case of any institution specified in the order.`
  line
  line `^11[Provided further that provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in the case of any educational`
  line `institution affiliated to the Indraprastha Vishwavidyalaya incorporated under the Indraprastha`
  line `Vishwavidyalaya Act, 1998.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 3,ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 5, for "beyond a radius of ten miles from the Convocation Hall of the University".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for State of Delhi.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 5, for "that limit".`
  line
  line `5. Proviso omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1981, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-6-1981).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 53 of 1966, s. 27 (w.e.f. 22-4-1969).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 5, for "aforementioned limit".`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "that limit".`
  line
  line `10. For notifications directing that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to certain institutions, see Gazette of`
  line `India, 1922, Pt. I, p. 491; and, ibid., 1923, Pt. I, pp. 259, 459 and 498.`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 43 of 2002, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-8-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47680)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `University open to all classes, castes and creeds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47680&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The University shall be open to all persons`
  line `of either sex and of whatever race, ^1[creed, caste or class], and it shall not be lawful for the University`
  line `to adopt or impose on any person any test whatsoever of religious belief or profession in order to`
  line `entitle him to be admitted thereto as a teacher or student, or to hold any office therein, or to graduate`
  line `thereat, or to enjoy or exercise any privilege thereof, except ^2*** in respect of any particular`
  line `benefaction accepted by the University, where such test is made a condition thereof by any`
  line `testamentary or other instrument creating such benefaction:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent religious instruction being given in`
  line `the manner prescribed by the Ordinances to those ^3[who have consented to receive it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 6, for "creed or class".`
  line
  line `2. The words "where such test is specially prescribed by the Statutes, or," omitted by s. 6, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "not unwilling to receive it by persons (whether teachers of the University or not) approved for that`
  line `purpose by the Executive Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47681)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Teaching of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47681&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) All recognized teaching in connection with the University`
  line `courses shall be conducted under the control of the Academic Council by teachers of the University,`
  line `and shall include lecturing, laboratory work and other teaching conducted in accordance with any`
  line `syllabus prescribed by the Regulations.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) The authorities responsible for organizing such teaching shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(4) The courses and curricula shall be prescribed by the Ordinances and, subject thereto, by the`
  line Regulations.
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (2) rep. by Act 24 of 1943, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 5 of 1952, s. 7`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (47682)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47682&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [7A. Visitor.--(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor shall have the right to cause an inspection to be made by such person or persons as`
  line `he may direct of the University, its buildings, laboratories and equipment and of any institution`
  line `maintained by the University, and also of the examinations, teaching and other work conducted or`
  line `done by the University and to cause an inquiry to be made in like manner in respect of any matter`
  line `connected with the University.`
  line
  line `(3) The Visitor shall in every case give notice to the University of his intention to cause an`
  line `inspection or inquiry to be made, and the University shall be entitled to appoint a representative who`
  line `shall have the right to be present and be heard at such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(4) The Visitor may address the Vice-Chancellor with reference to the result of such inspection and`
  line `inquiry, and the Vice-Chancellor shall communicate to the Executive Council the views of the Visitor`
  line `with such advice as the Visitor may offer upon the action to be taken thereon.`
  line
  line `(5) The Executive Council shall communicate through the Vice-Chancellor to the Visitor such`
  line `action, if any, as it is proposed to take or has been taken upon the result of such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Executive Council does not, within a reasonable time, take action to the satisfaction`
  line `of the Visitor, the Visitor may, after considering any explanation furnished or representation made by`
  line `the Executive Council, issue such directions as he may think fit and the Executive Council shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(7) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section the Visitor may, by order in`
  line `writing, annul any proceeding of the University which is not in conformity with this Act, the Statutes`
  line `or the Ordinances:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order he shall call upon the University to show cause why`
  line `such an order should not be made and, if any cause is shown within a reasonable time shall consider`
  line `the same.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_b:
  sectionId (47683)
  sectionNo 7B
  orderNo 9
  title `Chief Rector and Rectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47683&sectionno=7B&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[7B. Chief Rector and Rectors.-- (1) The Chief Commissioner of the ^2[Union territory of Delhi]`
  line `shall be the Chief Rector of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) Such persons, as may be appointed in this behalf in accordance with the Statutes, shall be`
  line `Rectors of the University.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for "State of Delhi".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47684)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 9, for item (iv).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47684&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the officers of the University:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Chancellor,`
  line
  line `(ii) the Pro-Chancellor,`
  line
  line `(iii) the Vice-Chancellor,`
  line
  line `^1[(iv) the Pro-Vice-Chancellor, if any,]`
  line
  line `(vi) the Treasurer,`
  line
  line `(vii)The Registrar,`
  line
  line `(viii) the Deans of the Faculties, and`
  line
  line `(ix) such other persons in the service of the University as may be declared by the Statutes to be`
  line `officers of the University.`
