  string
  line `[Removal of names of registered graduates.] Rep. by the Delhi University (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1952 (5 of 1952), s. 24.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (47716)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Disputes as to constitution of University authorities and bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47716&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises`
  line `whether any person has been duly elected or appointed as, or is entitled to be, a member of any`
  line `authority or other body of the University, the matter shall be referred to the Chancellor, whose`
  line `decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (47717)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Constitution of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47717&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Where any authority of the University is given power by this Act`
  line `or the statutes to appoint committees, such committees shall, save as otherwise provided, consist of`
  line `members of the authority concerned and of such other persons (if any) as the authority in each case may`
  line `think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (47718)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Filling of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47718&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `All casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio`
  line `members) of any authority or other body of the University shall be filled, as soon as conveniently may`
  line `be, by the person or body who appointed, elected or co-opted the member whose place has become`
  line `vacant, and the person appointed, elected or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be a member of such`
  line `authority or body for the residue of the term for which the person whose place he fills would have`
  line `been a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (47719)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Proceedings of University authorities and bodies not invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47719&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No act or`
  line `proceeding of any authority or other body of the University shall be invalidated merely by reason of the`
  line `existence of a vacancy or vacancies among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (47720)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Conditions of service of officers and teachers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1952, s. 25, for section 45.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47720&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[45. Conditions of service of officers and teachers.-- (1) Every salaried officer and teacher of`
  line `the University shall be appointed under a written contract, which shall be lodged with the University`
  line `and a copy thereof shall be furnished to the officer or teacher concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the University and any of its officers or teachers`
  line `shall, at the request of the Officer or teacher concerned or at the instance of the University, be referred`
  line `to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Executive Council, one member nominated by the officer or teacher concerned and an umpire appointed by the Visitor, and`
  line `the decision of the Tribunal shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (47721)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Pension and provident funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352&sectionId=47721&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00039_192208_1523344160352
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The University shall constitute, for the benefit of its`
  line `officers, teachers, clerical staff and servants, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes, such pension, insurance and provident funds as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such pension, insurance or provident fund has been so constituted, ^1[or where any`
  line `such pension, insurance or provident fund has been constituted by a college under rules which have`
  line `been approved by the Central Government,] the Central Government may declare that the provisions`
  line `of the Provident Funds Act, ^2[1925 (19 of 1925), shall apply to such funds, as if it were a`
  line `Government Provident Fund.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1943, s. 14.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1940, s. 3, for "1897".`
  line
  line `3. The heading "TRANSITORY PROVISIONS" omitted by Act 24 of 1943, s. 15.`
